other_tests.findings: Mild bibasilar atelectasis in the visualized lung bases, no pleural effusion. Labeled as normal: liver, portal veins, gallbladder, pancreas, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, duodenum, loops of small bowel, and urinary bladder. Prominent appendix measuring 7 mm in diameter with equivocal periappendiceal fat stranding and tiny mesenteric nodes in the right lower quadrant. No free air, fluid or lymphadenopathy in the intra-abdominal cavity or pelvis.
